Preheat greased grill to medium heat. Mix meat, 2 tablespoons of the steak sauce, onion and garlic. Shape into 6 patties. Mix dressing and remaining 2 tablespoon. steak sauce; set aside. Grill patties 7 to 9 minutes on each side or until cooked through (160 degrees F). Spread bottom half of each bun with 1 tablespoon of the dressing mixture; cover with burger and top of bun.